parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine failure can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: white smoke pouring out of the exhaust

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve spring failure can cause engine misfires, rough idling, and loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents and engine damage.
Engine stalling can cause loss of control, increased risk of accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Power Steering Motor Coupler Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Power Steering Motor Coupler can cause the steering wheel to clunk and lock up when turning, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel clunks or makes unusual noises when turning
the steering wheel locks up or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse lockout mechanism can cause the vehicle to accidentally shift into reverse while moving forward or attempting to shift into first gear, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle can shift into reverse while moving forward
the vehicle can shift into reverse while attempting to shift into first gear
the driver can accidentally shift into reverse during the shifting process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The jerky and violent downshifting can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the transmission, and can be a safety concern, especially when coming to a stop.
An engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Flames or smoke coming from the engine
unusual noises or smells from the engine.
